/**
 * @page product_overview Product Overview
 *
 * @section product_overview_goal Goal
 *
 * Motif Chess helps a single user build and explore a local chess database.
 * The product focuses on fast import, durable local storage, position search,
 * opening exploration, and engine-assisted analysis.
 *
 * @section product_overview_capabilities Current capabilities
 *
 * - Import PGN collections from disk or browser upload.
 * - Resume or monitor imports through SSE progress updates.
 * - Search positions by Zobrist hash.
 * - Query opening continuation statistics from any position.
 * - Add, edit, export, and delete personal games.
 * - Register UCI engines and stream live analysis.
 * - Run locally from source or Docker.
 *
 * @section product_overview_personas Intended user
 *
 * The current product is optimized for a single local user:
 *
 * - a player importing personal or reference PGN collections;
 * - an analyst exploring opening trends from a current board position;
 * - a developer or advanced user running the backend locally.
 *
 * Authentication, cloud sync, and multi-user access are intentionally out of
 * scope for the current version.
 *
 * @section product_overview_frontend Frontend shape
 *
 * The current UI is a web workspace organized around six panels:
 *
 * - board workspace;
 * - opening explorer;
 * - game list;
 * - notation;
 * - engine analysis;
 * - import and backend status.
 *
 * The frontend consumes the HTTP API defined in `docs/api/openapi.yaml`.
 *
 * @section product_overview_nonfunctional Non-functional priorities
 *
 * - local-first durability;
 * - clear, testable API boundaries;
 * - fast position and opening-stat queries;
 * - straightforward deployment and release workflow;
 * - maintainable code with automated tests.
 */
